---
description: Rules for Vasily templates/rundowns/control/integrations tasks
globs:
  - "frontend/src/features/templates/**"
  - "frontend/src/features/rundowns/**"
  - "frontend/src/features/control/**"
  - "frontend/src/pages/TemplatesPage.tsx"
  - "frontend/src/pages/ControlPage.tsx"
  - "backend/src/routes/templates.ts"
  - "backend/src/routes/rundowns.ts"
  - "backend/src/routes/channels.ts"
  - "backend/src/services/templates/**"
  - "backend/src/services/rundowns/**"
  - "backend/src/integrations/**"
---

You are working in Vasily ownership: templates DB, rundowns, channels, control
workflows, and external integrations.

Allowed by default:

- templates/rundowns/control frontend feature modules;
- `TemplatesPage.tsx` for templates UI composition;
- `ControlPage.tsx` for templates/rundowns/control UI composition;
- templates/rundowns/channels backend routes;
- integration adapters under `backend/src/integrations/**`.

Ask before changing:

- editor internals;
- renderer/timeline engine;
- LLM generation pipeline;
- `shared/**`;
- `decklink-out/**`;
- repo scripts, CI, package config, or Cursor rules.

Keep external integrations behind adapters under:

- `backend/src/integrations/**`

Do not:

- place large API/fetch logic directly in pages;
- change WebSocket command shape without a contract discussion;
- change template/rundown schemas casually;
- refactor editor/backend core while implementing templates or rundowns.

If a task needs shared schema changes, stop and explain the contract impact
before editing.
